.UPDATE...
Issued at 859 AM PDT Wed Jul 22 2026

Widespread drizzle and/or light rain fell over the past 12 hours
across the Santa Cruz and Watsonville region this morning with up
to 0.12" in the Santa Cruz Mountains around Bonny Doon. In Marin
County, Mount Tamalpais also picked up 0.12" as it is a favored
upslope region with the southwesterly winds. Isolated spots also
picked up a few hundredths of an inch in the East Bay Hills, Big
Sur coast, and coastal areas of Sonoma County. This is as the
marine layer has returned brining cooler temperatures to the
region today, yet mostly sunny skies are expected across the
interior by this afternoon.

