.LONG TERM...
Issued at 148 AM PDT Wed Jul 22 2026
(Thursday through Tuesday)

More typically drier (gradually less humid) summer weather
develops Thursday onward to the weekend, along with onshore
breezes, night and morning low clouds and fog and possibly
patchy drizzle. High pressure may compress the marine layer over
the weekend bringing a slight warming trend to inland areas.

The latest ECMWF and GFS show dry conditions in the 700-500 mb
layer, mostly if not entirely dominated by mid-latitude winds
over our forecast area for the next 10 days. Any daytime heating
potential instability will be capped by thermal and height ridging
at least out through 84 hours according to the 00z NAM model.

