.AVIATION...
(18Z TAFS)
Issued at 1039 AM PDT Wed Jul 22 2026

An onshore gradient and 1800 ft deep marine layer have kept cigs
in place over coastal terminals. Latest satellite imagery depicts
a rapidly eroding cloud deck over inland area while coastal
stratus persists. Winds remain out of the south to southwest and
will gradually veer back to west and NW through the day as the
clouds retreat back to the coast. Anticipate an early return to of
the marine layer this evening.

Vicinity of SFO...Moderate and occasionally gusty southerly winds
will prevail through the morning hours as marine layer hovers near
the terminal. Southerly wind have help keep the skies mostly MVFR
to IFR. Cigs are expected to make an early return as winds veer to
the northwest this afternoon.


SFO Bridge Approach...Similar to SFO.

Monterey Bay Terminals...MVFR Cigs are expected to persist through
the remainder of the morning then temporarily scatter out in the
early afternoon before returning around sunset this evening.

